[[File:Wankishi ike cropped Totomi Koseki Zue Frame 22.jpg|thumb|300px|{{ill|Tōtomi Province|ja|遠江国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōtomi Province|qq=}} {{ill|Sano District|ja|佐野郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sano District|qq=}} {{ill|Tomibe Village|ja|富部村|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomibe Village|qq=}}’s Lending Bowl Legend as depicted in a color painting from the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo period|qq=}} (from the edition of “Wangan Ike” by {{ill|Fujichōkō|ja|藤長庚|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujichōkō|qq=}} in the {{ill|Tōtomi Ancient Monuments Illustrated Collection|ja|遠江古蹟圖會|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōtomi Ancient Monuments Illustrated Collection|qq=}}, 1803; held by the {{ill|National Diet Library|ja|国立国会図書館|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/National Diet Library|qq=}})]]
'''Lending Bowl Legend''' (わんかしでんせつ) is a collective term for a type of folk tale and traditional narrative – one of the narrative types of folklore – whose central theme is a story in which meal trays ({{ill|Meal Tray|ja|膳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meal Tray|qq=}}) or bowls ({{ill|Bowl|ja|椀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bowl|qq=}}) are borrowed from mounds, abysses, large rocks, or caves in the shady parts of mountains.<ref>柳田國男『定本 柳田國男集 第五巻』筑摩書房, 1977, 第14刷, p.230</ref>

== Examples of the Lending Bowl Legend ==
{{Quote|In a place called Kanaya, there was a large rock, and when one shouted beside that rock, “Lend me meal trays and bowls for as many people as I need,” the next morning the desired number of trays and bowls were prepared. One time, when an ungrateful person returned fewer bowls than he had borrowed, he was never lent any again.|{{ill|Tottori Prefecture|ja|鳥取県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tottori Prefecture|qq=}} {{ill|Hattō District|ja|八頭郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hattō District|qq=}}’s tradition|『昔話伝説小事典』, みずうみ書房, 1987, p.273}}

